The paper deals with streaming algorithms for coverage problems, which are typically studied in the area of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). The paper also introduces a new sketching technique, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The results are also relevant to the area of computational complexity (cs.CC), as the paper discusses the optimality of the algorithms.
